%N A393137 a(n) is the number of nontrivial divisors {d | n, 1 < d < n} that are sum-irreducible, for n >= 1; by convention a(0) = 0.
%C A393137 Recall that d is sum-irreducible if there is no subset of the other nontrivial divisors of d that sums to d (A392650).
%F A393137 a(n) = card({d : d | n, 1 < d < n, d is sum-irreducible}).
%e A393137 For n = 36, the divisors are {1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 9, 12, 18, 36}. Among these, the sum-irreducible nontrivial ones are {2, 3, 4, 6, 9}. Thus a(36) = 5.
%o A393137 (Python)
%o A393137 # The function 'is_sum_irreducible' is defined in A392650.
%o A393137 from sympy import divisors
%o A393137 def A393137(n: int) -> int:
%o A393137     if n == 0: return 0
%o A393137     divs = divisors(n)[1:-1]
%o A393137     irr_divs = [d for d in divs if is_sum_irreducible(d)]
%o A393137     return len(irr_divs)
%o A393137 A = [A393137(n) for n in range(89)]; print(A)
%Y A393137 Cf. A392650
%K A393137 nonn
